task.summary: Default task
Fixed minor regression bug that was interfering with certain LDAP queries.
Tweak some command line utilities. Changed a constructor.
Fixed bad help entry.

reworked all of the online help in the CLI. Changed which database field is used for VOs rather than deal with possible collisions. Added command to the approval component of the CLI to list approved or unapproved clients.
Added some more telemetry to track down how issuer was set.
Forcing documentation update to get latest on website.
Updated versio number for release
Updates to documentation. Changes to FNAL scripts to assert different claims.
Fixes for FNAL CIL-971

CIL-974 fixes: more exception types for various JWT verification failures so understandable error messages can be generated and logged. User info, refresh token and token exchange now have far less byzantine ways to get the signing key and to generate understandle messages for the manifold failure opportunities available now.
CIL-974, CIL-976
CIL-985, CIL-947
Last minute commits before branching. CIL-607.
Overdue cleanup now that release is cut.
Small usability tweaks.
Made command line client a bit more terse. More updates to testing-readme.txt
Broke off WLCG groups support into its own script
Fixes for CIL-1012, CIL-1002. Updated testing-readme.txt and tests to reflect changes. All clients (including OIDC, public and admin) are now traceable individually.
Added flag for debug util for better looking log entries. Refactored FNAL QDL scripts.
CIL-1002, CIL-1012, CIL-1014, CIL-1019. Had to move some classes for package visibility
CIL-1011 support. Final checkin of stuff before cutting 5.1.4.
Usability tweak to CLI. CIL-1025 fixed.
Updated CLI archive and admin unlink commands.
Updated testing readme. Found a bug in a QDl utility which is now fixed.
CIL-934 work on CLC so it can be tested with augmented scopes. Lots of revision on blurb about writing claim source handlers and examples.
More documentation updates. Changed an example class.
CIL-934 (device flow) and CIL-1035 (refresh tokens created when client does not allow them). Documented device flow servlet configuration too.
CIL-934 (device flow) part 2
CIL-934 (device flow) part 3
Improved database access for cache rebuild (RFC 8628). Fixed several small issues with device flow. Had to refactor some code because inheritance was not helpful. More tests!
Mostly fixed edge cases in template resolution uncovered while documenting it.
test tweaks. Updated website and documentation.
Updated versions for 5.2.0 release.
Fixes to QDL scripts for LIGO clients.
CIL-607, a few improvements to the command line client.
Mostly quality of life issues for the CLI. Added support for storing a result set and using it. Added tiny tweak to parser, which caused the whole thing to get rebuilt.
Mostly quality of life issues for the CLI part 2. Added more searches for clients and their approval status.
Resurrected Derby. Reworked some tests that were old. Added OA4MP specific QDL test harness. Not a lot there yet, but more is coming.
CIL-1047 CIL-1051 fixes.
For SciAuth. Good standard example to have for documentation anyway.
Tidying up before 5.2.1
Added RFC 7636 support. Updated a command utility for SciAuth.
CIL-1072. ID token not consistently being saved after timestamp update
updated java mail jar. Updated documentation.
Changed the name of a (badly named) method that has been bugging me since May of 2012. CIL-738: Added token introspection endpoint to .well-known document.
New GA4GH V 2 passport support. Added API call the client management to get all clients managed by a given admin.
CIL-1092 support. Updated GA4GH version 2 script. CIL-646, discovery entry for revocation and introspection endpoints.
